<emphasis id="6B8D534DFFB3FFDFFCF7FD2AFA8BFD3E" box="[862,1355,652,676]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="281">
Distribution and ecology. – 
<taxonomicName id="9EF9F4DCFFB3FFDFFBD8FD2BFA8BFD3E" authorityName="Callm., Buerki, Munzinger &amp; Lowry" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Callm., Buerki, Munzinger &amp; Lowry" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[1137,1355,652,676]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Neoarytera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="12" pageNumber="281" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nekorensis">Neoarytera nekorensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is endemic to the Nekoro forest in the centre-west region of Grande Terre, where it grows in sclerophyll forest on black clay soil (
<bibRefCitation id="3D68F2AEFFB3FFDFFCE8FD4BFC1BFC9E" author="TURNER, H." box="[833,987,748,772]" pageId="12" pageNumber="281" refId="ref12575" refString="TURNER, H. (1995). Cladistic and biogeographic analyses of Arytera Blume and Mischarytera gen. nov. (Sapindaceae) with notes on methodology and a full taxonomic revision. Blumea, Suppl. 9." type="book" year="1995">TURNER, 1995</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
